                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/4001: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-29T17:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 29, 1926—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 30—12:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>65. Referring to telegram of Ceiba, October 28, 7 p.m. President Paz this
                    afternoon in my presence and that of the Minister of Foreign Affairs directed
                    the Ministry of War immediately to telegraph Ceiba authorities to order the <hi
                        rend="italic">mayor de plaza</hi> to parade 100 soldiers in front of the
                    American consulate and salute its flag, then in the presence of the Governor and
                    the commandant to apologize to the vice consul and to his Government; after
                    which the mayor is to be court-martialed.</p>
                <p>President Paz and the Minister of Foreign Affairs expressed deep regret over the
                    unfortunate incident.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Ceiba.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
